<workout_file>
  <author>Gravel God Training</author>
  <name>T5_Pogacar-Stack_L3_7reps</name>
  <description>[UAE / Pogacar Torque-VO2 + Sprint. Three demands, incomplete recovery]
PROGRESSION: Level 3/4

WARM-UP:
-15-20min progressing Z1-&gt;Z2
-1x10min high-cadence Z3 @100-120rpm (wake up leg speed before the grind)
-then 2-3x30s spin-up openers

MAIN SET:
-7 reps, each = 2:30 @110% at 48-52rpm
  -&gt; straight into a 15s ALL-OUT sprint (~180%)
-Recovery = high Zone 2 (~70%), NOT full rest, 3min

PURPOSE:
Stacks high torque + VO2 power + a neuromuscular spike under accumulating fatigue. Advanced.

EXECUTION:
-Seated for torque, stand into the sprint. The short Z2 'recovery' is part of the stimulus - keep pedalling.

SOURCE:
-UAE Team Emirates-XRG (Jeroen Swart); Cycling Weekly / Cinch.

NUTRITION:
-40-70g carbs/hr.

HYDRATION:
-500-750ml/hr.</description>
